FATO designation marking H01/H19 instead of H02/H20 to avoid misinterpretation during radio communication with ATC. The geographical coordinates of helicopter stands are not published in AIP. The stand protection area is 28m in diameter instead of 34m required. Simultaneous operations on Heliport West are not allowed due to overlapping of safety areas. It is the Pilot's responsibility to avoid simultaneous operations between: - Helicopter stands and adjacent helicopter stand - Helicopter stands and FATO - FATO and the taxilane SIERRA Hover taxi is only allowed along runways, taxiways and heliport west. Hover taxi is forbidden at the GAC Sectors 1,2,3 and 4 as well as over all aircraft stands. Detailed charts: VFR Manual
